Find the sum of numbers from 1 to n (user enters n).

Take a list as input and check if it has duplicate elements.

Take 5 numbers from the user and print the maximum and minimum.

Check if a given string is a palindrome.

Check if a given number is prime.

Print the first n terms of the Fibonacci series.

Print numbers from 1 to 100 that are divisible by 3 or 5.

From a list, create a new list containing squares of all even numbers.

Count the number of vowels and consonants in a sentence.

Make a countdown program using a while loop (start from user input and go to 1).

Given a list of numbers, print the factorial of each element.

🔵 Tricky / logical

